Raymond B. West https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Raymond_B._West 0 Raymond B. West (February 11, 1886 – September 11, 1923) was an American motion picture director. He joined the New York Motion Picture Company in 1910 and directed more than 70 motion pictures between 1910 and 1919 before suffering a nervous breakdown that forced him to retire from the business. He died in 1923 at age 37. Raymond_B._West ( February_11_,_1886 – September_11_,_1923 ) was an_American_motion_picture_director .
